# Lightweight Visual Token System (Astro + Tailwind)

## Core priority

- SEO and minimal initial JavaScript are more important than visual complexity.
- Do not add a React UI library for static UI.
- Public UI must stay Astro-first.
- React is allowed only for islands that truly need interaction.
- Header, sidebar, footer, cards, alerts, buttons, inputs, layout sections, FAQs, breadcrumbs, and SEO content must be Astro + Tailwind unless there is a strong reason.

## Design system enforcement

- Do not use random one-off values for radius, border, shadow, focus ring, spacing, or component heights.
- Define reusable CSS variables in `src/styles/tokens.css`.
- Import `tokens.css` from the global stylesheet.
- Use tokens through Tailwind arbitrary values, for example:
  - `rounded-[var(--radius-xl)]`
  - `border-[var(--border-muted)]`
  - `shadow-[var(--shadow-xs)]`
- No component may define raw color, radius, border, or shadow values directly unless it is the token file.

## Required token names

Define all of the following tokens in `src/styles/tokens.css`:

- `--radius-xs`
- `--radius-sm`
- `--radius-md`
- `--radius-lg`
- `--radius-xl`
- `--radius-2xl`
- `--radius-full`

- `--border`
- `--border-muted`
- `--border-strong`

- `--ring`
- `--ring-soft`

- `--shadow-xs`
- `--shadow-sm`
- `--shadow-md`
- `--shadow-lg`

- `--header-height`
- `--sidebar-width`
- `--sidebar-collapsed-width`

- `--control-sm`
- `--control-md`
- `--control-lg`

## Radius scale

- `--radius-xs: 0.375rem;` (6px)
- `--radius-sm: 0.5rem;` (8px)
- `--radius-md: 0.625rem;` (10px)
- `--radius-lg: 0.75rem;` (12px)
- `--radius-xl: 1rem;` (16px)
- `--radius-2xl: 1.25rem;` (20px)
- `--radius-full: 9999px;`

## Radius usage rules

- Button: `--radius-md`
- Input: `--radius-md`
- Select: `--radius-md`
- Textarea: `--radius-md`
- Badge: `--radius-full`
- Small card: `--radius-lg`
- Standard card: `--radius-xl`
- Main form shell: `--radius-2xl`
- Main tool panel: `--radius-2xl`
- Alert/warning box: `--radius-lg`
- Sidebar item: `--radius-md` or `--radius-lg`
- Modal/sheet/popover: `--radius-2xl`
- Do not use `rounded-3xl` everywhere.
- Do not use random radius values such as `rounded-[13px]`, `rounded-[18px]`, or `rounded-[22px]`.

## Border tokens and usage

- `--border` for normal component borders.
- `--border-muted` for cards, layout separators, and header/sidebar/footer borders.
- `--border-strong` for emphasized states.
- `--ring` for focus border color.
- `--ring-soft` for focus ring background.

Rules:

- Default border width is 1px.
- Header uses `border-bottom`, not shadow.
- Sidebar uses `border-right`, not shadow.
- Footer uses `border-top`, not shadow.
- Cards use `border-[var(--border-muted)]`.
- Inputs/selects/textareas use `border-[var(--border)]`.
- Important panels may use `border-[var(--border)]`.
- Dangerous/warning states must use semantic warning/danger tokens, not random colors.
- Do not use shadow as the primary way to separate layout sections.

## Focus states

- Every interactive element must have a visible focus state.
- Focus style must use `var(--ring)` and `var(--ring-soft)`.
- Focus must be visible in both light and dark mode.
- Do not remove outline unless replaced with an accessible visible focus style.

## Shadow scale and usage

- `--shadow-xs` for rare subtle cards.
- `--shadow-sm` for hover/elevated cards only when necessary.
- `--shadow-md` for dropdowns/popovers.
- `--shadow-lg` for modals/sheets.
- Default cards should usually have no shadow or only `--shadow-xs`.
- Header/sidebar/footer must not use shadow.
- Do not use heavy shadows on public SEO pages.

## Component height rules

- Button sm: 36px minimum height.
- Button md: 44px minimum height.
- Button lg: 48px minimum height.
- Input/select md: 44px minimum height.
- Large form controls may use 48px.
- Icon button: 44px by 44px.
- Mobile touch targets must be at least 44px.

## Spacing rules

- Use a limited spacing scale.
- Small inner gaps: 8px or 12px.
- Form field gaps: 12px to 16px.
- Card padding: 16px mobile, 20px to 24px desktop.
- Main form shell padding: 16px mobile, 24px desktop.
- Section vertical spacing: 40px to 48px mobile, 64px to 80px desktop.
- Avoid random padding values.

## Button rules

- Buttons must use shared `src/components/ui/Button.astro` for static Astro UI.
- Button radius must be `--radius-md`.
- Button must not use box-shadow by default.
- Allowed variants:
  - `primary`
  - `secondary`
  - `outline`
  - `ghost`
  - `danger`
  - `soft`
- Primary button is for the main action only.
- Danger button is only for destructive or risky actions.
- Wallet connect buttons must not import wallet libraries directly.
- Static `Button.astro` must not include JavaScript.

## Input and form control rules

- Inputs, selects, and textareas must use shared Astro or React field components based on context.
- Static/simple fields can be Astro.
- Tool forms inside React islands can use React field components.
- Inputs must use `--radius-md` and `--border`.
- Disabled fields must look disabled and explain why when needed.
- Error state must use semantic danger tokens.
- Focus state must use `--ring` and `--ring-soft`.

## Card rules

- Cards must use shared `src/components/ui/Card.astro` for static UI.
- Standard card radius is `--radius-xl`.
- Main tool/form cards use `--radius-2xl`.
- Cards use border before shadow.
- Cards should use background tokens like `var(--card)` or `var(--surface)`.
- Do not overuse glassmorphism, blur, or gradients.
- Public content cards must be readable without JavaScript.

## Alert and warning rules

- Alerts use `--radius-lg`.
- Alert tones must be semantic:
  - info
  - warning
  - danger
  - success
- Risky Solana actions must include visible warnings.
- Do not rely on color alone for danger/warning states.
- Include concise explanatory text.

## Sidebar, header, and footer rules

- Must be mostly Astro/static HTML.
- Use borders for separation.
- No heavy shadows.
- No global wallet provider.
- No global Reown initialization.
- No Solana SDK imports.
- No React UI kit for static navigation.
- Sidebar active state should use subtle background, border, or text/icon color.
- Sidebar item radius should be `--radius-md` or `--radius-lg`.
- Mobile drawer may be a tiny island only if needed.

## Animation rules

- No global animation library.
- No Framer Motion for static layout.
- Use only simple CSS transitions when needed:
  - `transition-colors`
  - border/background transitions
- Avoid transform-heavy hover effects.
- No decorative animations on SEO pages.

## Dark and light mode

- All tokens must support light and dark mode.
- Do not hardcode dark mode colors in components unless using tokens.
- Borders in dark mode must be visible but soft.
- Focus rings must remain visible in dark mode.
- Cards and forms must have enough contrast in both themes.

## Implementation requirements

When applying this rule, update existing components to use the token system and create or update:

- `src/styles/tokens.css`
- `src/components/ui/Button.astro`
- `src/components/ui/Card.astro`
- `src/components/ui/Input.astro`
- `src/components/ui/Alert.astro`

Constraints:

- Keep these components JavaScript-free.
- Do not introduce new runtime dependencies for these static components.
- Do not install Ant Design, MUI, Chakra, HeroUI, or any full React UI kit.
- `shadcn/ui` may only be used selectively inside React islands for complex accessible components such as Dialog, Sheet, Popover, Tooltip, Command, or complex Select.
- Do not use `shadcn/ui` for static layout components.

## Bundle and architecture guardrails

- Public pages must render meaningful HTML without JavaScript.
- Header/sidebar/footer must not import React UI libraries.
- Initial public page bundle must not include wallet/Reown/Solana/Raydium/Meteora/Jito/heavy crypto libraries.

## Acceptance checklist

- Buttons/cards/inputs/alerts use tokens instead of random one-off values.
- Light and dark mode are visually consistent.
- Focus states are visible and accessible.
- Mobile touch targets are at least 44px.
- No unnecessary animation.
- No shadow-heavy static layout.
